/**
 * Static dataset of buildable Palworld 1.0 base structures and their material costs.
 *
 * Costs and icon tokens were sourced from palworld.gg/structures (July 2026). This is a broad
 * set covering the full Wooden/Stone/Metal/Ancient building sets, the production tiers
 * (workbenches, furnaces, assembly lines, generators, mining sites), storage, Pal facilities,
 * infrastructure, food/farming, defense, lighting, and the Antique furniture set.
 *
 * It is NOT the game's complete 490+ list: palworld.gg paginates its structure list in the
 * browser (server-side ?page= isn't supported), and the other full-data sources online are from
 * pre-1.0 patches. So rather than guess costs for the ~360 structures that don't render (which
 * is exactly what caused the earlier breeding-rank bugs), this includes only entries whose costs
 * were actually verifiable. It's easy to extend: add a [Structure] to [allStructures] and the
 * paginated UI picks it up automatically.
 *
 * Icons (both structures and materials) are hotlinked from palworld.gg and loaded at runtime,
 * matching the Pal-icon approach; nothing is bundled. `techLevel` of null = available from start.
 */
